ackedByMap` and `toProxyBeanSupportsUnderscoreFallbackAndFluentSetter` to cover those aspects.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering data conversion**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the need to get the age as an integer from the string \\\"42.\\\" It seems like a straightforward conversion, but I also need to ensure that if I'm mapping this value, it should be serializable. I should double-check that, because if it's not serializable, there's an issue that needs to be addressed. Writing some code will likely help clarify how to handle this situation effectively.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3WoMGYL74e3MqyO16kUB2XAq|fc_0303c5ec4408054b0169f44387da30819da4db30e9b221015d", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cn.hutool/hutool-all/5.8.25/src/test/java/cn_hutool/hutool_all/MapProxyTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cn_hutool.hutool_all;\n\nimport cn.hutool.core.map.MapProxy;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.util.LinkedHashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class MapProxyTest {\n    @Test\n    public void createsProxyBeanThatReadsValuesFromMap() {\n        Map<String, Object> values = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        values.put(\"name\", \"Hutool\");\n        values.put(\"age\", \"21\");\n        values.put(\"active\", \"true\");\n        values.put(\"given_name\", \"Core\");\n\n        PersonView person = MapProxy.create(values).toProxyBean(PersonView.class);\n\n        assertThat(person.getName()).isEqualTo(\"Hutool\");\n        assertThat(person.getAge()).isEqualTo(21);\n        assertThat(person.isActive()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(person.getGivenName()).isEqualTo(\"Core\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void proxyBeanSetterWritesBackToMapAndReturnsProxy() {\n        Map<String, Object> values = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        PersonView person = MapProxy.create(values).toProxyBean(PersonView.class);\n\n        PersonView returned = person.setNickname(\"toolkit\");\n\n        assertThat(returned).isSameAs(person);\n        assertThat(values).containsEntry(\"nickname\", \"toolkit\");\n        assertThat(person.getNickname()).isEqualTo(\"toolkit\");\n    }\n\n    public interface PersonView {\n        String getName();\n\n        int getAge();\n\n        boolean isActive();\n\n        String getGivenName();\n\n        String getNickname();\n\n        PersonView setNickname(String nickname);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1301, "output": 1012, "cacheRead": 11776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 14089, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777615739484, "responseId": "resp_0303c5ec4408054b0169f4437bd0c8819dbc63a61cdd8fed40"}}
